51:45.620 --> 51:48.760
how do we democratize a boundary we can't touch?

51:49.180 --> 51:53.620
We have to force open the technocratic boundaries to the interior plenum.

51:53.620 --> 51:57.100
In the computational terms of sphere pop,

51:57.620 --> 52:03.080
we have to insert new, massive events into the append-only history

52:03.080 --> 52:07.080
that alter the fundamental grammar of the outer scope.

52:07.580 --> 52:08.060
Wait, like what?

52:08.180 --> 52:11.640
We have to make the operational rules of the central banks,

52:11.880 --> 52:14.840
the credit rating bodies, the sovereign debt servicers,

52:15.180 --> 52:18.440
completely visible and legally revisable by the public.

52:18.660 --> 52:21.940
We have to shatter the insulation of pure economics.

52:21.940 --> 52:24.680
We have to demand admin access.

52:25.080 --> 52:27.560
So you have to drag the root code out of the server room

52:27.560 --> 52:30.420
and into the user interface so we can actually vote on it.

52:30.760 --> 52:32.360
We have to politicize the central bank.

52:32.460 --> 52:33.560
That is requirement one.

52:34.100 --> 52:35.020
Break the insulation.

52:35.580 --> 52:36.820
What is the second requirement?

52:37.300 --> 52:41.520
The second requirement focuses on expanding the entropy field we talked about earlier.

52:42.260 --> 52:47.800
Mathematically, this is modeled by increasing what the paper calls logistic variation.

52:48.340 --> 52:49.740
Okay, no raw equations.

52:49.740 --> 52:53.120
Well, walk me through the concept of logistic variation.

52:53.440 --> 52:55.040
What does it look like on the ground?

52:55.480 --> 53:00.120
It relates to an individual's position relative to complete market dependence.

53:00.840 --> 53:03.240
Imagine a scale from zero to one.

53:03.780 --> 53:07.780
If you are pushed to the extreme boundary values,

53:08.020 --> 53:09.360
meaning you are at zero,

53:10.200 --> 53:14.360
having absolutely nothing and completely dependent on wage labor to survive,

53:14.360 --> 53:18.360
or you are at one, completely saturating the resources,

53:18.860 --> 53:20.840
the mathematical variation collapses.

53:21.380 --> 53:22.400
There is no entropy.

53:22.880 --> 53:23.860
There is no choice.

53:24.220 --> 53:30.120
Austerity operates by continually driving the working class down to that extreme boundary

53:30.120 --> 53:31.980
of complete exclusion,

53:32.700 --> 53:33.800
driving them toward zero.

53:33.920 --> 53:35.380
You either have absolutely nothing

53:35.380 --> 53:38.280
and must accept whatever grueling labor terms are offered,

53:38.480 --> 53:39.920
or you own everything.

53:40.060 --> 53:41.100
There is no middle ground.

53:41.200 --> 53:42.280
There is no breathing room.

53:42.280 --> 53:46.660
Right, but mathematical variation reaches its absolute maximum

53:46.660 --> 53:49.680
when you are exactly in the middle of that scale.

53:49.840 --> 53:53.460
That is the point of greatest internal variation and freedom.

53:53.680 --> 53:56.340
So to expand the entropy field in reality,

53:56.600 --> 54:01.420
we must enact policies that aggressively raise the subsistence floor.

54:01.420 --> 54:05.140
We are talking about implementing universal basic income,

54:05.800 --> 54:09.380
building robust public housing that isn't tied to employment,

54:10.160 --> 54:12.700
guaranteeing free health care and education.

54:13.200 --> 54:16.940
We have to pull people away from the extreme boundary of zero

54:16.940 --> 54:21.760
so they aren't forced into the wage labor pinball flippers just to survive.

54:22.200 --> 54:27.180
We must maximize the variation in how people can safely choose to live.

54:27.180 --> 54:29.620
We untilt the pinball machine.

54:30.060 --> 54:31.620
We make the landscape flatter.

54:32.400 --> 54:36.900
So the vector flow of human effort can comfortably explore the whole board,

54:37.440 --> 54:40.060
finding new ways to collaborate and create,

54:40.480 --> 54:44.180
rather than just plummeting in a state of terror into the wage labor flippers.

54:44.560 --> 54:44.840
Yes.

54:45.480 --> 54:49.060
Raising the floor creates the space for alternative economies to breathe.

54:49.480 --> 54:53.020
And that leads to the third and final mathematical requirement,

54:53.360 --> 54:56.480
weakening the coupling between the boundary and the interior.

54:56.480 --> 54:58.920
What does coupling mean in this context?

54:59.480 --> 55:03.680
It refers to how strongly the institutional memory those boundary signals

55:03.680 --> 55:06.360
forces its will onto the present landscape.

55:06.880 --> 55:09.060
Currently, the coupling is incredibly strong.

55:09.560 --> 55:11.740
The boundary constantly beams the message,

55:12.340 --> 55:15.520
enforce wage labor, protect creditors at all costs,

55:15.920 --> 55:17.560
punish inflation with unemployment.

55:18.100 --> 55:20.840
We must weaken or redistribute this coupling

55:20.840 --> 55:27.500
so that the institutions amplify high-entropy signals rather than low-entropy ones.

55:28.040 --> 55:30.940
So instead of the central bank having a mandate that says,

55:31.320 --> 55:33.680
